haps because of this, Gregory has hitherto been somewhat neglected by historians - a gap which this book aims to fill. It provides a full account of his contribution to the Crusade, demonstrating that he left a lasting mark on how crusading would operate in the years to come. PHILIP BALDWIN eceived his doctorate from Queen Mary, University of London.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChurch historyyMiddle Ages, 600-1500. 4aHistory of Religion. 4aMedieval History. 4aMilitary History. 7aRELIGION / History.2bisacsh  aByzantine emperor.  aCrusades.  aCrusading movement.  aDiplomat.  aIlkhan of the Mongols.  aMamluk Sultan Baybars.  aPhilip Baldwin.  aPolitical impact.  aPope Gregory X.  aThirteenth century.  aWestern Europe.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311143136940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781782042716?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782042716423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782042716/original  a978-3-11-143136-9  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles